{
  "texts": [
    "This method enhances the convolutional recurrent neural network by recognizing the interconnections among the various factors involved in assessing the quality of text.",
    "The linguistic features used to create linguistically informed models include part of speech (POS), universal dependency relations, structural well-formedness, lexical diversity, sentence cohesion, causality, and informativeness of the text.",
    "Incorporating rating information: The consideration of rating information in the design of AES methods plays a significant role in enhancing the performance of the neural models.",
    "However, representing rating information and fuse it with essay content has been a challenge in the process of designing AES models.",
    "Liang et al. (2018) proposed a Siamese bidirectional LSTM architecture to capture semantic features of the essays and the rating criteria information embedded within them."
  ]
}